         <entry xml:id="DRMorrisonetal_ScalpayDRMorrisonmisc10-idp119977264">
            <form>
               <orth>duathal</orth>
            </form>
            <def>something difficult to describe or the mixture that it was to describe; obscurity that it was to me… I cannot describe.]</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="DRMorrisonetal_ScalpayDRMorrisonmisc10-idp120009880">
            <form>
               <orth>duathar-neulach</orth>
            </form>
            <def>shadow of clouds.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="DRMorrisonetal_ScalpayDRMorrisonmisc10-idp119966968">
            <form>
               <orth>duathar</orth>
            </form>
            <def>shadow (perhaps from dubhar). Thàinig duathar air co-dhiù.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="DRMorrisonetal_ScalpayDRMorrisonmisc10-idp119971000">
            <form>
               <orth>cròiseanta</orth>
            </form>
            <def>sound of singing through the nose. Tha guth aige cho cròiseanta – nasal. [SLIP: Nasal (singing through nose).]</def>
         </entry>
