         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="DRMorrisonetal_ScalpayDRMorrisonmisc10-idp119889208">
            <form>
               <orth>maide-ramasagaidh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>a wooden plunger, on end, to burst open a door (perhaps relative to the day of the wooden sailing boats or… I remember hearing it). [NOTES: the slip has ‘maide-ramasgaidh’. Definition: A wooden “plunger” (battering-ram?) to burst open a door.]</def>
         </entry>
